quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  36,13,"And strike for them a similitude: the companions (i.e., the inhabitants) of the town, as the Emissaries came to it"
  36,14,"As We sent to them two (men). Yet they cried them lies, so We reinforced them with a third. Then they said, \"Surely we are (sent) to you as Emissaries"
  36,15,"They said, \"In no way are you anything except mortals like us; and in no way has The All-Merciful sent down anything; decidedly you do nothing except lie"
  36,16,"They said, \"Our Lord knows that surely we are indeed Emissaries to you"
  36,17,And in no way is there anything (incumbent) on us except the evident Proclamation
  36,18,"They said, \"Surely we augur ill of you. Indeed in case you do not give over, indeed we will definitely stone you, and indeed there will definitely touch you from us a painful torment"
  36,19,"They said, \"Your bird (of augury) is with you; is it so, in case you are reminded? (i.e., Do you call it an evil omen that we remind you?) No indeed, (but) you are an extravagant people"
  36,20,"And (there) came from the remotest part of the city a man going speedily. He said, \"O my people, closely follow the Emissaries"
  36,21,"Closely follow (the ones) who ask of you no reward, and they are rightly-guided"
  36,22,"And for what should I not worship Him who originated me, and to Him you will be returned"
  36,23,"Shall I take to myself, apart from Him, gods whose intercession, in case The All-Merciful wills any adversity to me, will not avail me anything, nor will they rescue me"
  36,24,"Lo, surely (in that case) I should indeed be in evident error"
  36,25,"Surely I believe in your Lord, so hear me"
  36,26,"It was said, \"Enter the Garden!\" He said, \" Oh, would that my people knew"
  36,27,"With what (Grace) my Lord has forgiven me, and He has made me among the honored"